  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Maternal and Child Health Integrated Program: Lesotho Voluntary Medical Male Circumcision (VMMC)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MCHIP is working with the Lesotho Ministry of Health (MOH) to increase human resources for national VMMC scale up, strengthen MOH capacity to coordinate VMMC services by providing training and mentorship, and to ensure that VMMC strategies and programs are evidence-informed by improving the quality of data collection tools and processes.  MCHIP has been scaling up facility-based VMMC and early infant male circumcision (EIMC) services in public and private facilities and hospitals. This includes assessing and upgrading facilities, conducting training to providers of VMMC and EIMC, and also directly providing VMMC services in supported sites through MCHIP staff teams.  In order to assure that these facilities are utilized fully, MCHIP is working work MOH and partners to increase the demand for VMMC and EIMC services.  The program and the communications strategy specifically includes addressing gender-related barriers and service related issues such as counseling and post-operative risk reduction.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Men and their families</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to support the Ministry of Health in Lesotho to scale up VMMC services as part of the national HIV prevention strategy.</narrative>
  </description>
